Special correspondent Malcolm
Brabant is in
Rome for us, and sent us this
preview.

38:27.905 --> 38:32.677 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MALCOLM BRABANT: After the
Manchester bomb
attack, Italy's security status
remains the

38:32.710 --> 38:34.578 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
same, on high alert.

38:34.612 --> 38:39.283 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
The Vatican is always
well-protected, but
it's locked down tighter than
usual for the

38:39.317 --> 38:45.556 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
duration of President Trump's
meeting with
the leader of the world's 1.2
billion Catholics.

